        <tr><td>Average Western intake</td><td>~13g/day</td><td>~16g/day</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p>Most adults are consuming roughly half the recommended amount. This "fibre gap" is one of the most consistent nutritional shortfalls in modern diets.</p>
